<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/369.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-07T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 2, 10 a.m. You are instructed to inform Theodore that the
                            United States will refuse to regard as legal any such issue of paper
                            money as he proposes.</p>
                        <p>French and German Ambassadors in Washington have been advised in this
                            sense, in order that their nationals in Haiti may be informed. You may
                            show this telegram to your French and German colleagues.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>